es\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n;Official campaign websites\n* [https://www.shannonbray.us/ Shannon Bray (L) for Senate]\n* [https://www.calfornc.com/ Cal Cunningham (D) for Senate] \n* [http://www.thomtillis.com/ Thom Tillis (R) for Senate]\n\n{{2020 United States elections}}\n\n[[Category:United States Senate elections in North Carolina|2020]]\n[[Category:2020 United States Senate elections|North Carolina]]\n[[Category:2020 North Carolina elections|United States Senate]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox election\n| election_name      = 2020 United States Senate election in North Carolina\n| country            = North Carolina\n| type               = presidential\n| ongoing            = yes\n| previous_election  = 2014 United States Senate election in North Carolina\n| previous_year      = 2014\n| next_election      = 2026 United States Senate election in North Carolina\n| next_year          = 2026\n| election_date      = November 3, 2020\n| image1             = [[File:Thom Tillis Official Photo.jpg|x150px]]\n| nominee1           = [[Thom Tillis]]\n| party1             = Republican Party (United States)\n| popular_vote1      = \n| percentage1        = \n| image2             = [[File:James \"Cal\" Cunningham (cropped 2).jpg|x150px]]\n| nominee2           = [[Cal Cunningham]]\n| party2             = Democratic Party (United States)\n| popular_vote2      = \n| percentage2        = \n| map_image          = \n| map_size           = \n| map_caption        = County results\n| title              = U.S. Senator\n| before_election    = [[Thom Tillis]]\n| before_party       = Republican Party (United States)\n| after_election     = \n| after_party        = \n}}\n{{ElectionsNC}}\n\nThe '''2020 United States Senate election in North Carolina''' will be held on November 3, 2020, to elect a member of the [[United States Senate]] to represent the [[North Carolina|State of North Carolina]], concurrently with the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 U.S. presidential election]], as well as [[2020 United States Senate elections|other elections]] to the United States Senate in other states and [[2020 United States House of Representatives elections|elections]] to the [[United States House of Representatives]] and various [[2020 United States elections|state and local elections]]. North Carolina is one of just 5 states which is holding a presidential, gubernatorial, and senatorial election concurrently in 2020.  On March 3, 2020, Republican incumbent Sen. Thom Tillis and former State Sen. Cal Cunningham won their respective parties' primaries.<ref name=\"PrimaryNight\">{{cite web |title=NC SBE Contest Results |url=https://er.ncsbe.gov/?election_dt=03/03/2020&county_id=0&office=FED&contest=2867 |website=er.ncsbe.gov |publisher=North Carolina Board of Elections |accessdate=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Republican primary==\n===Candidates===\n====Nominee====\n*[[Thom Tillis]], incumbent U.S. Senator<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cohen|first1=Zach C.|title=How 2014's Outsiders Became 2020's Insiders|url=https://www.nationaljournal.com/s/675089/how-2014s-outsiders-became-2020s-insiders|publisher=National Journal|date=December 5, 2018|accessdate=December 5, 2018}}</ref>\n\n====Eliminated in primary====\n*Larry Holmquist, candidate for U.S. Senate in [[2016 United States Senate election in North Carolina#Republican primary|2016]]<ref name=\"Repprimary\">{{cite web |last1=Robertson |first1=Gary D. |title=N Carolina candidates rush for legislature, Meadows' seat |url=https://www.newsobserver.com/news/state/north-carolina/article238598733.html |website=Raleigh News & Observer |accessdate=December 20, 2019 |date=December 20, 2019}}{{dead link|date=January 2020}}</ref>\n*Sharon Hudson, activist<ref name=\"Repprimary\"/>\n*Paul Wright, former [[North Carolina Superior Court]] judge, [[perennial candidate]], and candidate for U.S. Senate in [[2016 United States Senate election in North Carolina#Republican primary|2016]]<ref name=\"Repprimary\"/>\n\n====Withdrawn====\n*Sandy Smith, farm owner<ref>{{cite news|last1=Woolverton|first1=Paul|title=Near-death experience inspires Eric Mansfield to consider US Senate race|url=https://www.fayobserver.com/news/20190417/near-death-experience-inspires-eric-mansfield-to-consider-us-senate-race|newspaper=The Fayetteville Observer|date=April 17, 2019|accessdate=April 26, 2019}}</ref> ''([[2020_United_States_House_of_Representatives_elections_in_North_Carolina#District_1|running for U.S. House in NC-01]])''\n*Garland Tucker, former [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] and chairman of Triangle Capital<ref>{{cite web |last1=Path\u00e9 |first1=Simone |title=Garland Tucker drops Senate primary challenge to North Carolina's Thom Tillis |url=https://www.rollcall.com/news/campaigns/garland-tucker-drops-primary-challenge-to-north-carolinas-thom-tillis |website=Roll Call |accessdate=December 2, 2019 |date=December 2, 2019}}</ref>\n====Declined====\n*[[Mark Meadows (North Carolina politician)|Mark Meadows]], former U.S. Representative for [[North Carolina's 11th congressional district]]<ref>{{cite tweet|last=Frey|first=Kevin|user=KevinFreyTV|number=1123229569471926273|title=In interview with @costareports, Rep. Mark Meadows says there's \"zero chance\" he will primary @SenThomTillis, but says he believes Tillis will have a \"legitimate\" primary opponent #ncpol|date=April 30, 2019|accessdate=April 30, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ted Budd]], incumbent U.S. Representative for [[North Carolina's 13th congressional district]]<ref name=\"Tillisprimary\">{{cite news|last1=Wong|first1=Scott|last2=Bolton|first2=Alexander|title=GOP's Tillis comes under pressure for taking on Trump|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/senate/433929-gops-tillis-comes-under-pressure-for-taking-on-trump|publisher=The Hill|date=March 13, 2019|accessdate=March 13, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mark Walker (North Carolina politician)|Mark Walker]], incumbent U.S. Representative for [[North Carolina's 6th congressional district]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Scott |last2=Wilson |first2=Reid |title=NC rep explores Tillis primary challenge |url=https://thehill.com/homenews/state-watch/473018-nc-rep-explores-tillis-primary-challenge |website=The Hill |accessdate=December 4, 2019 |date=December 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Endorsements ===\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Thom Tillis\n| list = \n;Federal officials\n*[[Donald Trump]], [[List of Presidents of the United States|45th]] [[President of the United States]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/1143645216907378695|title=Senator Thom Tillis of North Carolina has really stepped up to the plate. Thom is tough on Crime, Strong on the Border and fights hard against Illegal Immigration. He loves our Military, our Vets and our great Second Amendment. I give Thom my Full and Total Endorsement!|work=Twitter|author=Donald J. Trump}}</ref>\n*[[Lindsey Graham]], U.S. Senator (R-SC)<ref>{{cite web|title=Sen. @ThomTillis stood with me against the liberal mob to confirm Justice Kavanaugh, and he will continue to stand for @realDonaldTrump's agenda of a strong military, lower taxes, and conservative judges. This is why I strongly urge my neighbors in NC to re-elect @ThomTillis.|url=https://twitter.com/LindseyGrahamSC/status/1136981131662962689|website=Twitter|author=Lindsey Graham}}</ref>\n*[[Marsha Blackburn]], U.S. Senator (R-TN)<ref>https://twitter.com/VoteMarsha/status/1234482083109777410</ref>\n*[[John R. Bolton|John Bolton]], former [[United States National Security Advisor]]<ref>https://nypost.com/2019/09/13/john-bolton-returns-to-former-position-as-head-of-two-pacs/</ref> \n*[[Nikki Haley]], former [[United States Ambassador to the United Nations]] and former [[Governor of South Carolina]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ThomTillis/status/1230635125282615296|title=So thankful to have Ambassador @NikkiHaley\u2019s support. She has been a strong leader on sound, conservative priorities and I am honored to have her on o