phy|first=Brian|title=National Democrats make their pick in North Carolina's Senate primary|url=https://www.newsobserver.com/news/politics-government/election/article236855688.html|publisher=[[The News & Observer]]|date=October 31, 2019|accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[End Citizens United]]<ref>{{cite tweet|last=Arkin|first=James|user=JamesArkin|number=1156236391992516609|title=End Citizens United endorses Cal Cunningham in #NCSen. They\u2019ve also endorsed Dem candidates in ME IA AZ NM and TX.|date=July 30, 2019|accessdate=July 30, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[International Brotherhood of Electrical Workers|International Brotherhood of Electrical Workers and Carolina Electrical Workers Association]]<ref name=\"CalEndorsements\"/>\n* [[J Street PAC]]<ref>{{cite web |title=JStreetPAC Candidates |url=https://donate.jstreetpac.org/candidate-directory/ |website=JStreetPAC}}</ref>\n*[[League of Conservation Voters]]<ref>{{cite tweet|last=Voters|first=League of|user=LCVoters|number=1156623650415665154|title=LCVAF is proud to endorse @CalforNC to represent NC in the Senate! As a veteran and entrepreneur, Cunningham knows the national security & economic threats of #climatechange. He has the experience that is needed to help advance our #cleanenergy future in the Senate. #NCSen|date=July 31, 2019|accessdate=August 10, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[National Committee to Preserve Social Security and Medicare]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Richtman|first=Max|title=National Committee Endorses Cal Cunningham in NC Senate Race|url=https://www.ncpssm.org/documents/pac/national-committee-endorses-cal-cunningham-in-nc-senate-race/|date=October 29, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[North Carolina Association of Educators]]<ref>{{cite tweet|last=Cunningham|first=Cal|user=CalforNC|number=1226887764974632960|title=I\u2019m ready to get to work partnering with educators across our state to secure the resources needed in our public schools. In the Senate, I\u2019m committed to doing what it takes to give all students the sound