e<br>size{{efn|name=\"Key\"}}\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Thom<br>Tillis (R)\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Erica D.<br>Smith (D)\n! Undecided\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://www.meredith.edu/assets/images/content/meredith_college_poll_report_oct_2019.pdf#page=16 Meredith College]\n| September 29 \u2013 October 7, 2019\n| 996\n| \u00b1&nbsp;3%\n| 33%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}| '''34%'''\n| 17%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [http://emersonpolling.com/2019/06/04/north-carolina-2020-biden-with-early-lead-on-trump-and-democratic-primary-field/ Emerson College]\n| May 31 \u2013 June 3, 2019\n| 932\n| \u00b1&nbsp;3.1%\n| 39%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}| '''46%'''\n| 15%\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;text-align:center;\"\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size{{efn|name=\"Key\"}}\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Thom<br>Tillis (R)\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Generic<br>Democrat\n! Undecided\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [http://static.politico.com/3e/86/e3bf575445e9bd0e3c777a5916a0/ppp-save-my-care-poll-of-north-carolina.pdf Public Policy Polling (D)]{{efn-ua|Poll sponsored by Save My Care|name=\"SMC\"}}\n| June 30 \u2013 July 1, 2017\n| 1,102\n| \u00b1&nbsp;3.6%\n| 44%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}| '''48%'''\n| 8%\n|}\n{{collapse bottom}}\n\n=== Results ===\n{{Election box begin\n | title      = United States Senate election in North Carolina, 2020}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n | party      = Republican Party (United States)\n | candidate  = [[Thom Tillis]] (incumbent)\n | votes      = \n | percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n | party      = Democratic Party (United States)\n | candidate  = [[Cal Cunningham]]\n | votes      = \n | percentage = \n | change     = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n | party      = Libertarian Party (United States)\n | candidate  = Shannon Bray\n | votes      = \n | 